08/04/2004
ATHENS, Greece -- The European Commission said Wednesday (7 April) that Greece's budget deficit could rise to 3.2 per cent of GDP, well over the 3 per cent EU ceiling.
Economy and Finance Minister Giorgos Alogoskoufis acknowledged that the situation is much more serious than previously thought and accused the Socialist government of irresponsible management.
In other news, Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis said Wednesday that the Olympics would be completely safe despite the "choking deadlines" organisers face as a result of construction delays.
Preparations are behind at two major sites, the Olympic Village and the port of Piraeus.
(AP, AFP, ANA, MPA - 07/04/04)
